We offer two certificate programs for academic credit.Both the Water Treatment Plant Operation Specialist Certificate Program and the Wastewater Treatment Plant Operation Specialist Certificate Program are designed for operators and students interested in earning academic credit from a university that may be transferred to other colleges/universities. Registration requires university enrollment in Sacramento State&rsquo;s College of Continuing Education.
If you are not planning to transfer your academic units to a college degree program, and are interested in earning continuing education units (CEUs), our other course offerings can meet your needs.

&nbsp;
This online course is based on a California Stormwater Quality Association (CASQA) Best Management Practice handbook and is designed to provide continuing education for professional engineers, municipal and regulatory agency employees, developers, construction companies, and others to increase their knowledge of stormwater best management practices.
Students complete our course using a CASQA BMP handbook and a study guide on CD. The final exam is completed online, allowing for instant grade results.
